## Implementation Plan

### Problem
When an unsupported shell is detected (e.g. xonsh), the setup completions
message shows the literal string "unknown" — the internal ShellType value —
rather than the actual shell name the user set in $SHELL.

  Before: Completions: Your shell (unknown) is not directly supported
  After:  Completions: Your shell (xonsh) is not directly supported

### Solution
Add a `name: string` field to `ShellInfo` (in shell.ts) populated from
`basename($SHELL)` at detection time. Use `shell.name` in the two
user-facing completion messages in handleCompletions() instead of
`shell.type`. When $SHELL is unset, `name` falls back to the type string.

### Files changed
- src/lib/shell.ts      — added `name` field to ShellInfo, populated in detectShell()
- src/commands/cli/setup.ts — use shell.name in unsupported/fallback messages
- test/commands/cli/setup.test.ts — assert on the real shell name ("xonsh")
